1
00:00:18,009 --> 00:00:19,009
Excuse me.

2
00:00:19,134 --> 00:00:22,050
Can you give me a hand?
I'm looking for Scofield Road.

3
00:00:22,175 --> 00:00:24,493
The map says it's near
the rock quarry.

4
00:00:32,272 --> 00:00:33,652
Thanks for the help.

5
00:00:43,437 --> 00:00:44,453
Hello?

6
00:00:47,391 --> 00:00:49,466
Hello? Anybody back there?

7
00:01:14,536 --> 00:01:15,686
I told her...

8
00:01:16,376 --> 00:01:19,099
I told Leanne we couldn't live
without each other.

9
00:01:24,272 --> 00:01:26,252
But she wouldn't come back to me.

10
00:01:28,995 --> 00:01:30,172
No, no. Wait...

11
00:01:45,787 --> 00:01:47,956
Nice to see you again, Mrs. Dubois.

12
00:01:48,849 --> 00:01:50,644
I hope I didn't frighten you.

13
00:01:50,914 --> 00:01:52,064
Agent Cooper?

14
00:01:52,422 --> 00:01:53,875
What are you doing here?

15
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,340
I told you I never
want to see you again.

16
00:01:56,550 --> 00:01:59,020
Actually,
I'm here to make a peace offering.

17
00:02:00,027 --> 00:02:03,408
Did you ever hear of a murderer
nicknamed "The Gentleman Caller"?

18
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:06,375
Abducted five young
women back in the 1980s?

19
00:02:06,922 --> 00:02:08,173
Never was caught.

20
00:02:08,661 --> 00:02:11,936
For a while now, the police have assumed
that he's either dead or in prison

21
00:02:12,061 --> 00:02:14,280
on some unrelated crime.

22
00:02:15,379 --> 00:02:16,517
They're wrong.

23
00:02:18,187 --> 00:02:20,788
The Gentleman Caller
is very much alive.

24
00:02:23,101 --> 00:02:24,935
Would you like his name and address?

25
00:02:27,501 --> 00:02:29,773
- What are you doing?
- I told you,

26
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,510
I'm attempting to make amends.

27
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:36,030
His name is Kyle Hawkins.

28
00:02:37,116 --> 00:02:38,266
Kyle Hawkins?

29
00:02:41,261 --> 00:02:43,477
When he would finish
with his victims,

30
00:02:44,131 --> 00:02:46,326
he liked to bury them
on the edge of Phoenix.

31
00:02:47,112 --> 00:02:48,420
The only problem is,

32
00:02:48,545 --> 00:02:50,606
a housing development is going up
at that location.

33
00:02:50,731 --> 00:02:52,424
They're breaking ground in a week.

34
00:02:53,747 --> 00:02:57,118
Tonight he's going to dig up
the remains of his girls

35
00:02:57,243 --> 00:02:59,162
and move them to a safer place.

36
00:02:59,592 --> 00:03:01,510
If you instruct the police

37
00:03:01,635 --> 00:03:04,642
to go to the very end of
Gayley Hill Drive

38
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:07,625
at approximately 8:30,
you'll catch him in the act.

39
00:03:09,985 --> 00:03:13,572
No ambiguity, Mrs. Dubois,
no room for deception.

40
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,380
Kyle Hawkins...

41
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:06,750
www.sub-way.fr
www.seriessub.com

42
00:04:14,654 --> 00:04:15,735
Kyle Hawkins?

43
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,682
That's what Agent Cooper
said his name was.

44
00:04:17,807 --> 00:04:19,425
Agent Cooper.
Tips from the dead.

45
00:04:20,215 --> 00:04:22,928
Well, he was one of
the FBI's best profilers.

46
00:04:23,297 --> 00:04:24,818
Emphasis on the "was."

47
00:04:24,943 --> 00:04:26,997
Look, I don't know how
seriously to take this either.

48
00:04:27,122 --> 00:04:29,972
The man certainly had no
problem lying to me in the past.

49
00:04:30,425 --> 00:04:32,646
On the other hand,
if what he's saying is the truth...

50
00:04:34,437 --> 00:04:37,110
I suppose we can spare
a couple of squad cars tonight.

51
00:04:37,235 --> 00:04:40,312
In the meantime, I'll see what I can
find out about this Hawkins fellow.

52
00:04:40,437 --> 00:04:42,656
See if there actually is
a Hawkins fellow.

53
00:04:44,427 --> 00:04:47,113
- Is there something else?
- Actually, there is.

54
00:04:48,477 --> 00:04:52,318
Just before I discovered Agent Cooper
in my kitchen, I had a dream about...

55
00:04:52,562 --> 00:04:54,975
I guess you could
call it a massacre.

56
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:57,489
It happened at a place
called Mike's Diner.

57
00:04:57,614 --> 00:05:00,364
Armed gunman went in,
shot everybody inside.

58
00:05:00,718 --> 00:05:03,500
I'm not sure where Mike's Diner is,
other than...

59
00:05:03,625 --> 00:05:06,120
it may be near a place
called Scofield Road,

60
00:05:06,245 --> 00:05:08,662
which is supposed to be
near a rock quarry.

61
00:05:08,971 --> 00:05:12,518
I have no idea when it happened,
or if it's happened yet,

62
00:05:12,971 --> 00:05:15,147
but it seemed to have occurred
during the daytime.

63
00:05:15,272 --> 00:05:17,983
Mike's Diner,
Scofield Road, rock quarry.

64
00:05:18,452 --> 00:05:20,570
And the shooter was upset
with his girlfriend...

65
00:05:20,695 --> 00:05:22,957
his ex-girlfriend... Leanne.

66
00:05:23,164 --> 00:05:24,406
She works there.

67
00:05:25,286 --> 00:05:26,686
One serial killer,

68
00:05:27,142 --> 00:05:30,003
one diner massacre... got it.

69
00:05:30,451 --> 00:05:31,651
Anything else?

70
00:05:33,419 --> 00:05:35,941
Thanks for coming all the way
to the airport to see me.

71
00:05:36,066 --> 00:05:37,868
Of course, you're the boss.

72
00:05:38,178 --> 00:05:39,422
Happy to do it.

73
00:05:41,244 --> 00:05:42,803
What brings you to Phoenix?

74
00:05:42,928 --> 00:05:44,593
Oh, refuel on the way to Japan.

75
00:05:44,992 --> 00:05:46,287
Oh. Cheers.

76
00:05:48,274 --> 00:05:51,517
I realized I had
a whole 45 minutes here.

77
00:05:51,642 --> 00:05:54,227
Thought maybe I'd use it
to talk to you about staffing.

78
00:05:54,352 --> 00:05:55,569
Staffing?

79
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,095
I want to hit you with a name.

80
00:05:59,421 --> 00:06:00,521
Hal Munzell.

81
00:06:02,657 --> 00:06:05,278
<i>After 20 years an arrest
has finally been made</i>

82
00:06:05,403 --> 00:06:07,616
<i>in the notorious
"Gentleman Caller" murders.</i>

83
00:06:07,883 --> 00:06:10,308
<i>Police, acting on an anonymous tip,</i>

84
00:06:10,433 --> 00:06:13,141
<i>discovered Kyle Hawkins
digging a hole...</i>

85
00:06:13,266 --> 00:06:14,456
Can you believe that?

86
00:06:14,712 --> 00:06:16,917
- What's that?
- Kyle Hawkins.

87
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:19,662
He was exactly where Agent Cooper said
he would be.

88
00:06:19,787 --> 00:06:22,771
Doing exactly what Cooper said
he'd be doing.

89
00:06:23,789 --> 00:06:26,468
Maybe he really is sorry.
Maybe he meant what he said.

90
00:06:26,878 --> 00:06:27,878
Maybe.

91
00:06:29,172 --> 00:06:32,901
Come on. I just helped solve
a 20-year-old murder case.

92
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:37,813
I'm sorry. I just can't understand why
Terry is so impressed with this guy.

93
00:06:38,474 --> 00:06:40,816
This is the most unspectacular
resume I've ever seen.

94
00:06:42,153 --> 00:06:44,445
Didn't you already call him,
ask him to come in?

95
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,650
Well, I left him a message.

96
00:06:47,391 --> 00:06:49,084
What choice did I have?

97
00:06:50,232 --> 00:06:53,219
Who knows, with any luck,
maybe he won't get back to me.

98
00:06:54,244 --> 00:06:55,624
I guess I spoke too soon.

99
00:06:55,749 --> 00:06:57,750
Nope, I don't think so.
I think it's mine.

100
00:07:03,542 --> 00:07:04,423
Hello.

101
00:07:04,548 --> 00:07:07,500
I'm guessing you're the reason
our esteemed D.A. sent me out here

102
00:07:07,625 --> 00:07:09,344
to visit Mike's Diner.

103
00:07:09,699 --> 00:07:11,333
You're kidding.
You're out there?

104
00:07:11,458 --> 00:07:12,514
<i>I just left.</i>

105
00:07:12,927 --> 00:07:15,617
<i>Had some excellent chicken pot pie,
too, by the way.</i>

106
00:07:15,742 --> 00:07:16,997
So everything's okay?

107
00:07:17,122 --> 00:07:19,354
<i>Well, it depends
how you define okay.</i>

108
00:07:19,522 --> 00:07:22,497
<i>That waitress you told Manny about,
Leanne, she's fine.</i>

109
00:07:22,804 --> 00:07:24,513
<i>So are all the people at the diner.</i>

110
00:07:24,638 --> 00:07:26,111
That's terrific news.

111
00:07:26,629 --> 00:07:28,874
Yeah, well, hold that thought.

112
00:07:30,725 --> 00:07:33,440
You don't happen to be anywhere
near a computer, do you? 'Cause...

113
00:07:33,565 --> 00:07:35,287
I'm about to send you an e-mail.

114
00:07:37,019 --> 00:07:38,019
<i>There.</i>

115
00:07:38,352 --> 00:07:39,770
<i>This guy look familiar?</i>

116
00:07:39,895 --> 00:07:42,226
Hold on,
I'm just getting the e-mail open.

117
00:07:47,002 --> 00:07:48,884
Oh, my God.

118
00:07:49,292 --> 00:07:51,553
This the guy you saw massacre
everyone at that diner?

119
00:07:53,685 --> 00:07:54,890
Everything all right?

120
00:07:55,058 --> 00:07:57,810
<i>I'm going to take that for a yes.
The guy's name was Adam Dietz.</i>

121
00:07:58,065 --> 00:08:01,444
Leanne gave us his address.
I guess the two of them are an item.

122
00:08:01,569 --> 00:08:03,260
No, were an item.

123
00:08:03,385 --> 00:08:05,963
Apparently she left him
after he lost his job.

124
00:08:06,207 --> 00:08:08,529
Poor guy was about
to lose his house, too.

125
00:08:09,052 --> 00:08:12,200
<i>Even left a handy suicide note,
lest there'd be any confusion</i>

126
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,279
<i>about what he did or why he did it.</i>

127
00:08:14,404 --> 00:08:17,704
So he never even went over there?
He never threatened anyone at all?

128
00:08:18,275 --> 00:08:19,263
Nope.

129
00:08:19,388 --> 00:08:21,043
Hey, that's the good news.

130
00:08:21,555 --> 00:08:23,627
Looks like the only life
this guy took was his own.

131
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:26,099
<i>I guess we'll compare
notes in the morning?</i>

132
00:08:26,224 --> 00:08:27,224
I guess.

133
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,857
No, wait, I don't want to do this.
Don't make me do this.

134
00:08:45,982 --> 00:08:48,492
Fine.
Shall I shoot you in the groin now?

135
00:08:49,242 --> 00:08:51,382
Adam, we talked about this.

136
00:08:51,883 --> 00:08:54,288
Either you hang yourself
or I shoot you six times.

137
00:08:54,413 --> 00:08:56,496
First shot in the groin.
We wait ten minutes.

138
00:08:56,621 --> 00:08:58,992
Second shot in the eye.
We wait another ten.

139
00:08:59,117 --> 00:09:01,900
- Third shot in the Adam's apple...
- All right, all right, I'm sorry!

140
00:09:02,025 --> 00:09:03,075
Never mind!

141
00:09:08,492 --> 00:09:09,492
Now jump.

142
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:13,413
Please, no, I don't think I can.
Don't make me do this.

143
00:09:13,748 --> 00:09:16,227
- I can't do this.
- You can do it, Adam, it's easy.

144
00:09:16,352 --> 00:09:18,619
Please, no!
Don't make me do this!

145
00:09:31,442 --> 00:09:33,178
Hi. Can I help you?

146
00:09:34,061 --> 00:09:36,867
Hal Munzell. I received your message
on my voice mail.

147
00:09:37,098 --> 00:09:39,411
Oh, right, yeah.
I asked you to call me.

148
00:09:39,749 --> 00:09:41,830
I know.
I thought this might be better.

149
00:09:43,097 --> 00:09:44,609
Oh, well, to be honest,

150
00:09:44,734 --> 00:09:47,389
I prefer to sort of set aside
some time and, you know...

151
00:09:47,514 --> 00:09:49,064
Is this a bad moment?

152
00:09:49,425 --> 00:09:50,839
Have you got an appointment?

153
00:09:51,322 --> 00:09:53,219
Am I disrupting something?

154
00:09:54,279 --> 00:09:56,004
No, it's all right. You're fine.

155
00:09:56,129 --> 00:09:58,388
Have a seat, Mr. Mun... Munzal?

156
00:09:59,054 --> 00:09:59,890
Munzell.

157
00:10:00,339 --> 00:10:01,339
Munzell.

158
00:10:02,617 --> 00:10:03,617
Okay.

159
00:10:04,809 --> 00:10:08,023
All right, yeah, I was looking...
I was looking at your résumé last night.

160
00:10:08,191 --> 00:10:09,241
Here we go.

161
00:10:13,355 --> 00:10:15,889
Well, I see that you moved
around quite a little bit.

162
00:10:16,014 --> 00:10:19,201
You don't seem to stay in one place for
very long and I just was curious why.

163
00:10:20,681 --> 00:10:24,382
I suppose that over time, I find
that I don't much like my colleagues,

164
00:10:25,053 --> 00:10:27,334
or perhaps they find
that they don't much like me.

165
00:10:32,035 --> 00:10:35,913
My boss, Terry Cavanaugh,
he took a real shine to you.

166
00:10:37,512 --> 00:10:38,762
Where did you two meet?

167
00:10:39,304 --> 00:10:40,736
We were at a conference.

168
00:10:40,861 --> 00:10:42,557
He made a pass
at the woman I was with.

169
00:10:47,649 --> 00:10:48,649
Okay.

170
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:54,786
I... I'm just starting to meet people,
and I see you're at...

171
00:10:54,911 --> 00:10:57,471
at Taylor-Hammond in Houston,
which is good,

172
00:10:58,076 --> 00:11:00,175
because it may be a while
before I figure out

173
00:11:00,300 --> 00:11:02,577
exactly which way I'm gonna go
with this position.

174
00:11:03,743 --> 00:11:06,081
You know, listen,
when I was on the plane with Terry...

175
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:09,439
- You were on the plane with Terry?
- He mentioned you were struggling

176
00:11:09,564 --> 00:11:12,296
with the dye sensitizer mechanisms
in your solar cell.

177
00:11:12,587 --> 00:11:15,123
And I put some thought into it,
and I came up with some ideas.

178
00:11:15,248 --> 00:11:17,287
Thought maybe you would
like to take a look.

179
00:11:17,412 --> 00:11:19,187
I don't know what to tell you,
Allison.

180
00:11:19,312 --> 00:11:22,468
- It just didn't look like a murder.
- It may not, but I'm telling you,

181
00:11:22,593 --> 00:11:24,482
that man was forced
to put that rope.

182
00:11:24,607 --> 00:11:27,632
And what about the note the guy left?
He was forced to write that, too?

183
00:11:27,757 --> 00:11:29,646
Yeah, as a matter of fact, I am.

184
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:33,417
Allison,
look at the physical evidence.

185
00:11:33,542 --> 00:11:36,846
There were no signs of forced entry, no
signs of struggle, no defensive wounds.

186
00:11:36,971 --> 00:11:39,833
And it's not like the guy didn't
have a reason to do what he did.

187
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:41,908
Allison,
what is it you'd like me to do?

188
00:11:42,178 --> 00:11:44,915
The only description you've given me is,
the guy was wearing a hoodie.

189
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,706
Do I haul in every male in the Phoenix
metro area who owns a hoodie?

190
00:11:48,186 --> 00:11:51,865
And need I remind you that just 24 hours
ago, you told me you saw the victim...

191
00:11:51,990 --> 00:11:54,758
the exact same guy I saw swinging
from a rafter last night...

192
00:11:54,883 --> 00:11:56,340
massacre a diner full of people?

193
00:11:56,848 --> 00:11:59,722
I'm sorry, no offense, but you're not
on your A game here, lady.

194
00:11:59,847 --> 00:12:02,280
I think maybe you just need
to take a step back.

195
00:12:02,405 --> 00:12:05,355
You'd be hard-pressed to find
a more unlikable human being.

196
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,985
- Don't hire him.
- I wouldn't, except for two things.

197
00:12:08,110 --> 00:12:11,863
My boss is championing the guy,
and these drawings are amazing.

198
00:12:12,231 --> 00:12:13,908
- What do you mean?
- Well, look,

199
00:12:14,033 --> 00:12:16,834
I couldn't figure out why Terry
would have anything to do with him,

200
00:12:16,959 --> 00:12:19,403
but now I look at the work,
I totally get it.

201
00:12:19,528 --> 00:12:22,340
I mean, this guy really
is a spectacular thinker.

202
00:12:22,884 --> 00:12:26,288
His solution for our dye sensitizer
problems really are amazing.

203
00:12:26,887 --> 00:12:29,094
I mean,
I don't think I have a choice.

204
00:12:30,831 --> 00:12:32,681
Okay, that's it. It's done.

205
00:12:33,922 --> 00:12:34,926
What's done?

206
00:12:35,051 --> 00:12:37,977
I just wrote Terry and told him
I'm hiring his friend.

207
00:12:38,602 --> 00:12:40,461
And then, I e-mailed Hal.

208
00:12:41,251 --> 00:12:44,158
Told him I'd be interested in having
him start as soon as possible.

209
00:12:44,283 --> 00:12:46,263
You really are a man of action.

210
00:12:46,388 --> 00:12:48,929
No, I just know
the inevitable when I see it.

211
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:52,561
Besides, you don't have to...

212
00:12:53,171 --> 00:12:55,321
like everyone you work with, right?

213
00:12:55,868 --> 00:12:57,758
I'm trying to build a company,

214
00:12:57,883 --> 00:12:59,213
not start a club.

215
00:13:00,196 --> 00:13:02,638
Spoken like a true
captain of industry.

216
00:13:03,287 --> 00:13:07,119
Which is great, 'cause it might
just be time for me to retire.

217
00:13:07,688 --> 00:13:09,387
What are you talking about?

218
00:13:09,650 --> 00:13:12,227
Well, I don't know.
It seems more and more lately,

219
00:13:12,352 --> 00:13:16,107
the things that I see, the things
that I dream, there's not a lot to them.

220
00:13:17,270 --> 00:13:19,458
If that's the case,
what's the point?

221
00:13:35,155 --> 00:13:36,355
Is this sleeplessness

222
00:13:36,525 --> 00:13:39,840
a product of your excitement over
the capture of the Gentleman Caller?

223
00:13:41,450 --> 00:13:42,709
Congratulations.

224
00:13:42,999 --> 00:13:44,175
No, thank you.

225
00:13:44,795 --> 00:13:47,325
We both know it wouldn't have
happened without your help.

226
00:13:47,693 --> 00:13:50,537
I'm just pleased that we've finally
begun to repair our relationship.

227
00:13:52,657 --> 00:13:55,803
You gave me some good information,
and I'm grateful,

228
00:13:55,928 --> 00:13:59,384
but I wouldn't call this...
this association a relationship.

229
00:14:03,182 --> 00:14:04,482
Michael Bradley.

230
00:14:10,725 --> 00:14:11,933
Who's Michael Bradley?

231
00:14:12,323 --> 00:14:16,062
A serial rapist with a predilection
for women with blonde hair.

232
00:14:16,548 --> 00:14:19,052
He's struck four times
over the last 18 months.

233
00:14:19,177 --> 00:14:21,943
Two of his victims were
high school students.

234
00:14:22,908 --> 00:14:25,354
The last girl
that he attacked fought back.

235
00:14:25,908 --> 00:14:28,698
And the police were able
to recover a hair sample.

236
00:14:29,468 --> 00:14:32,943
If they could locate this man
and procure some of his DNA,

237
00:14:34,416 --> 00:14:37,584
I think that they would find
a perfect match.

238
00:14:38,546 --> 00:14:41,373
Convicting him would be
a relatively simple matter.

239
00:14:42,134 --> 00:14:43,792
Tell me, Mrs. Dubois.

240
